#############################
AMI - Automated Mail Instalation
#############################

AMI is intended as an infrtrastructure to deploy and manage an E-mail server.

AMI has the following commands:
deploy        -used to deploy an E-mail server
add-record    -used to add a record
delete-record    -used to delete a record

By using AMI's parameters


#############################
# Configure
#############################
Usage: ./configure [OPTIONS]

Prepare the Linux host for the E-mail deployment.

Parameters that can be passed to the configuration script

-G [yes|no]         --If set to "yes" it will install ubuntu-desktop on ubuntu distributions. Reboot requiered.
                    Warning: Installing the Graphical User Interface will require a large
                    amount of disk space and the configuration process will take more time.

-O [yes|no]         --Installs the openssh-server package.

-r [yes|no]         --If set to [yes] it will configure the SSH service to allow root login with password

-w [yes|no]         --If set to [yes] appache2 package will be installed. Required for web interface administration.

